    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">517.24/841: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stewart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-09">September 9,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received September 10—3:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>546. Reference Department’s plain airgram of August 23, 1943, 7 p.m.,<note n="28"
                        xml:id="d257fn28">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_122">p. 122</ref>.</note>
                    Department’s circular telegram of August 31, 4:50 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>]
                        p.m.<note n="29" xml:id="d257fn29">Not printed.</note> and telephone call by
                    Mr. Brockman of the Department<note n="30" xml:id="d257fn30">John B. Brockman of
                        the American Hemisphere Exports Office.</note> to Mr. Edward B. Lawson,
                    Commercial Attaché, American Embassy, Managua, Nicaragua, September 7. The
                    Country Agency of Nicaragua approves the procedure recommended in Alternative
                    No. III for materials in free supply. Materials under estimate of supply and
                    those requiring priority assistance shall be processed in the present manner
                    requiring an Import Recommendation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
